          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #8\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    GitLab declares a coverage.xml artifact, but the pytest configuration generates terminal and HTML coverage only.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    Coverage artifact upload fails or silently disappears.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `.gitlab-ci.yml:23`\n- `.gitlab-ci.yml:27`\n- `pyproject.toml:340`\n- `pyproject.toml:347`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Add --cov-report=xml to GitLab pytest, or call make coverage.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
